im probably too late for this? haha.. but the reason why the current script is taking up RAM and crashes is because it is still sniffing + storing the massive ddos packages at TCP layer, even tho the firewall has blocked it.

Basic package flow:
`service provider firewall -> TCP -> system firewall (ufw / iptable) -> destination`

so a quick fix while waiting for the firewall to be ready is to tell the script not to store the package, this should keep the RAM usage below 100mb
```
sniff(filter="tcp port 8091", prn=log_connection, store=0)
```
